{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"916ff2e6-0ec7-471a-91d4-4012a54a88ce","content":"`[ExpectedException]` was **removed** in MSTest v4.\n\n**Replace it with `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` (or `Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<T>` for async methods).**\n\n### Before (v3)\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\n[ExpectedException(typeof(InvalidOperationException))]\npublic void DoWork_Throws() => _sut.DoWork();\n```\n\n### After (v4)\n```csharp\n[TestMethod]\npublic void DoWork_Throws() =>\n    Assert.ThrowsExactly<InvalidOperationException>(() => _sut.DoWork());\n\n// async version\n[TestMethod]\npublic async Task DoWorkAsync_Throws() =>\n    await Assert.ThrowsExactlyAsync<InvalidOperationException>(\n        () => _sut.DoWorkAsync());\n```\n\n### Key differences\n\n| | `[ExpectedException]` | `Assert.ThrowsExactly<T>` |\n|---|---|---|\n| Scope | Entire method | Specific lambda/action |\n| Derived types | Matches by default | Exact type only — use `Assert.ThrowsException<T>` if you want derived types too |\n| Inspecting exception | Not possible | Returns the exception instance |\n\n### Tip — inspect the exception\n```csharp\nvar ex = Assert.ThrowsExactly<ArgumentException>(() => _sut.Do(null));\nAssert.AreEqual(\"param\", ex.ParamName);\n```\n\nThis is a mechanical find-and-replace across your test files. Want me to do that automatically in your project?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"b5141ba8-0d86-4eea-bd81-a1199b6bc374","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking about migrating from MSTest v3 to v4, specifically about the `[ExpectedException]` attribute removal. Let me invoke the relevant skill for this.","outputTokens":449,"requestId":"1BD7:125F39:B8F01F:D0AC70:6A03F041"},"id":"2b719bdf-bf9b-4b26-a346-168f5b63ebc0","timestamp":"2026-05-13T03:30:19.483Z","parentId":"4f6acc6d-3aea-4529-9bf4-9f231dab2835"}
